libbsa

A free software library for reading and writing BSA files.

libbsa uses code from BSAOpt <https://github.com/Ethatron/bsaopt> to read and
write BSA files.

Note: This library is very much a work in progress and subject to significant
change. It is not release-ready.

libbsa is licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0. For the full
text of the license, see the included "LICENSE" file.

zlib modifications:
	build 'zlibvc', then 'zlibstat', removing ZLIB_WINAPI from its preprocessor definitions.